This paper deals with the integration of sub-6 GHz and mmWave technologies for wireless communication, which falls under the category of networked and internet-based systems (cs.NI). The paper also involves optimization of scheduling policies, which can be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also deals with the problem of intermittent connectivity and blockage, which can be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
